## Interaction Contract

- `total` takes precedence for page-count calculation with `pageSize`; `totalPages` is used when `total` is not provided.
- `showFirstLast` renders first/last page jump buttons, and boundary pages disable first/previous or next/last controls.
- The active page button exposes `aria-current="page"`; previous/next/first/last controls expose readable `aria-label` values.

## Best Practices

- Prefer `total + pageSize` so the UI can reflect item counts; use `totalPages` only when the backend cannot return totals.
- Keep `currentPage` one-based. Initialize the model to `1`, not `0`.
- Reset `currentPage` to `1` when filters or search terms change and the old page may be out of range.
- Keep pagination adjacent to the list or table it controls.
- Use the `info` slot for localized range copy such as “Viewing 21–40 of 120 items”.


## Dashboard Data Operations

Place pagination directly below the table and bind it to the same reactive model as filtering and selection; avoid floating pagination away from the list container.

::TuffDemoWrapper{demo="ComponentsDataOperationsDemo" code-lang="vue" title="Data operations panel" description="Pagination shares the data-region state with DataTable and Skeleton."}
---
code: |
  <template>
    <TxPagination
      v-model:current-page="page"
      :total="rows.length"
      :page-size="4"
      show-info
      show-first-last
    />
  </template>
---
::

